## Citation Workflow

### Adding Citations

1. Find paper (search databases or DOI)
2. Get BibTeX entry with all fields
3. Add to `references.bib`
4. Cite in paper.md using `[@key]`

### Citation Key Format

`firstauthorYEARkeyword`

| Example | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| `smith2023mortality` | Smith et al., 2023, mortality topic |
| `chen2024adipose` | Chen et al., 2024, adipose tissue |

### BibTeX Template

```bibtex
@article{firstauthor2024keyword,
  author    = {LastName, FirstName and LastName2, FirstName2},
  title     = {Full Article Title},
  journal   = {Full Journal Name},
  year      = {2024},
  volume    = {123},
  number    = {4},
  pages     = {567--589},
  doi       = {10.1234/journal.2024.12345},
  pmid      = {12345678},
}
```

### Citation Syntax

```markdown
Previous work [@smith2023].
Multiple sources [@jones2022; @chen2024].
Smith et al. [@smith2023] showed...
```

## Paper + Supplement Coordination

### What Goes Where

| Main Paper | Supplement |
|------------|------------|
| Key methods | Extended methods |
| Main results | Secondary analyses |
| 3-4 figures | Additional figures |
| 2-3 tables | Full data tables |

### Cross-Reference Format

```markdown
(see **Supplementary Methods**)
Results in **Supplementary Figure S1**
```

### Numbering
- Main: Figure 1, Table 1
- Supplement: Figure S1, Table S1

## Table Formatting

Tables are automatically formatted with borders via `format_docx.py`:
- Single-line black borders
- 6.5" width (fits margins)
- Bold header rows

## Figure Guidelines

- Format: PDF or PNG
- Resolution: 300+ DPI (600 preferred)
- Width: 3.5" (single) or 7" (full)

Include in markdown:
```markdown
![Figure 1. Caption.](figures/figure1.pdf){width=100%}
```

## Style Guidelines

### Numbers
- Spell out one through nine
- Numerals for 10+
- Always numerals with units

### Statistics
```
HR 2.27 (95% CI, 1.38-3.73; P = 0.001)
AUC 0.78 (95% CI, 0.72-0.84)
```

### Abbreviations
- Define on first use
- Standard: CI, HR, OR, AUC, SD

## Pre-Submission Checklist

- [ ] All citations resolve
- [ ] Figures ≥300 DPI
- [ ] Word count within limit
- [ ] Co-authors approved
- [ ] Data availability statement
- [ ] Ethics statement
- [ ] Conflict of interest
